    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Coiled baskets woven by Washoe Native North Americans, defined by a globular shape and tightly-coiled weave. Often made with willow, sedge, and other plant fibers. Well-known Washoe weaver Dat-So-La-Lee, also known as Louisa Keyser, (1835-1925) is often credited as repopularizing the degikup.</Note_Text>
